'''惠特尼美国艺术博物馆旧址'''（Whitney Museum of American Art original building）是[[纽约市|纽约市]][[曼哈顿|曼哈顿]][[格林尼治村|格林尼治村]]的3栋1838年的[[排屋|排屋]]，位于西[[八街|八街]]8-12号（[[第五大道|第五大道]]和麦克道尔街之间）。

1907年，葛楚德·范德伯爾特·惠特尼女士在西八街8号建立了惠特尼工作室画廊，毗邻她自己的麦克道尔巷工作室。这个，和后来西四街147号的惠特尼工作室俱乐部，旨在为年轻艺术家提供地方见面以及展示他们的作品。<ref name=nycland /><ref name=Whitney1937>{{cite book|last1=Whitney Museum of American Art|title=Whitney Museum of American Art: history, purpose and activities, with a complete list of works in its permanent collection to June, 1937|date=1937|publisher=Whitney Museum of American Art|location=New York|page=3|url=https://archive.org/details/whitneymuseumofa00whit|accessdate=7 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=ArtStory>{{cite web|last1=Wolf|first1=Justin|title=The Whitney Museum of American Art|url=http://www.theartstory.org/museum-whitney.htm|website=The Art Story|publisher=The Art Story Foundation|accessdate=7 February 2015|archive-date=2020-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928095635/https://www.theartstory.org/museum-whitney.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[File:Robert_Winthrop_Chanler,_Stained_Glass_windows_(one_of_seven)_in_the_Whitney_Studio,_New_York_City,_1918-1923._Private_Collection.jpg|thumb]]

1918年，美国艺术家罗伯特·温斯罗普 Chanler受托重新设计八街物业的内部，添加一个寓言人物的浮雕天花板，20英尺高的石膏和青铜壁炉，精心设计的花窗玻璃和装饰屏。<ref name=NatTreasure/><ref name=CeilingACL>{{cite web|title=Whitney Studio Ceiling|url=http://www.conlab.org/acl/whitney/sitehist.html|website=Architectural Conservation Laboratory (ACL) of the University of Pennsylvania|accessdate=4 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316185627/http://www.conlab.org/acl/whitney/sitehist.html|archive-date=2015-03-16|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name=ConservationPlan>{{cite web|last1=Matero|first1=Frank|last2=Drapala|first2=Lauren|title=THE WHITNEY STUDIO CEILING: Examination, Analysis and Recommendation for Conservation|url=http://www.conlab.org/acl/whitney/images/WHIT_Report_Final.pdf|website=Architectural Conservation Laboratory|publisher=University of Pennsylvania|accessdate=4 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150204041012/http://www.conlab.org/acl/whitney/images/WHIT_Report_Final.pdf|archive-date=2015-02-04|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

1929年，[[大都会艺术博物馆|大都会艺术博物馆]]拒绝了惠特尼赠送的近500件新作品，于是她建立了[[惠特尼美国艺术博物馆|惠特尼美国艺术博物馆]]。<ref name=WomenHistory>{{cite news|title=29: New York Studio School of Drawing, Painting and Sculpture|url=http://www.nps.gov/nr/travel/pwwmh/ny29.htm|accessdate=4 February 2015|work=Places where women made history|agency=National Park Service|archive-date=2020-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028123709/https://www.nps.gov/nr/travel/pwwmh/ny29.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref> 1931年，她聘请建筑师奥古斯特 L. 诺埃尔将西[[八街|八街]]8-12号的3栋1838年的[[排屋|排屋]]改造为画廊和自己的住宅，1936年改造为博物馆<ref name=nycland /><ref name=desrep />。

在20世纪40年代，有一个未实现的计划，将惠特尼的收藏品纳入[[大都会艺术博物馆|大都会艺术博物馆]]作为75周年庆典的一部分。<ref>[http://libmma.org/digital_files/archives/Met_Museum_75th_Anniversary_Committee_records_b18084369.pdf "Finding aid for the Metropolitan Museum of Art 75th Anniversary Committee records, 1945-1950"] {{Wayback|url=http://libmma.org/digital_files/archives/Met_Museum_75th_Anniversary_Committee_records_b18084369.pdf |date=20140728231351 }}, [[Metropolitan_Museum_of_Art|Metropolitan Museum of Art]]</ref>1954年，博物馆向北搬到第五大道和第六大道之间的54街新址；1966年又迁至[[麦迪逊大道|麦迪逊大道]]945号（东[[75街|75街]]）。

该建筑位于纽约市地标保护委员会于1969年设立的格林尼治村历史街区内, 并于1992年列为为[[国家历史地标|国家历史地标]]<ref name="nhlsum"/><ref name=NatTreasure>{{cite web|title=A National Treasure, the Gertrude Vanderbilt Whitney Studio|url=http://www.seniorwomen.com/news/index.php/whitney-studio-national-treasure|accessdate=4 February 2015|website=Senior Women Web|archive-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804060323/http://www.seniorwomen.com/news/index.php/whitney-studio-national-treasure|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nrhpinv">{{Cite journal|title=National Historic Landmark Nomination: Whitney Museum of American Art / New York Studio School of Drawing, Painting and Sculpture|url={{NHLS url|id=92001877}} |format=pdf|author=Avis Berman|date=December 2, 1991|publisher=National Park Service}} and 
